\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that minimum standards are complied with in respect of all criteria.\line \line The programme will also be offered through distance education and the evaluator notes that the same comments made in respect of the Advanced Certificate should apply. i.e. that the distance education mode at which this application is directed is under-developed. In this regard the evaluator observed that the learning guide does not effectively support Distance Education\'3B that it is sometimes not clear how support will be provided in a distance environment\'3B no adequate information is provided of how an orientation phase will be supported in distance education\'3B the institution has a detailed assessment policy and procedures but should ensure that it complements distance education adequately\'3B a practical component is included in the experiential learning policy\'3B however\'2C it is not stated how this will be overseen in a distance education setting\'3B the institution should ensure that they clarify sufficiently between distance and face-to-face modes of delivery. For the evaluator\'2C It is thus clear that the institution has failed to provide convincing evidence that it has the capacity to offer in the distance education mode of delivery. \line \line In the light of the concerns raised\'2C the Directorate does not support the recommendation that the programme should be accredited. It is recommended that the programme should not be accredited for the distance education mode of delivery. \line \cell \pard 

